    "content": [
      "Identify and use vocabulary words to describe how athletes move — pushing, pulling, spinning, and balancing.",
      "Categorise vocabulary as actions vs. things & directions using a two-column chart.",
      "Connect unit vocabulary to real-life contexts (skating, skiing, soccer)."
    ],
    "language": [
      "Produce and use the 15 target words: a force, happen, push, pull, a swing, a skater, forward, backward, spin, fall over, balance, down, connect, rub, friction.",
      "Distinguish nouns from verbs/adverbs in the vocabulary set.",
      "Use antonym pairs to review opposite meanings (forward/backward, push/pull, balance/fall over)."
    ]
